      <section name='book'>

         <para number='1' comment='locked book - try to open'>
         As you try to pry the book open, all you suceed in doing is scratching the surface. You notice an indentation on the front cover that looks like a beetle of some kind.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='open book after unlock'>
         The pages of the book are made of thick sheets of some kind of metal hinged together on the side, as you open the cover, holo images seem to hover over the pages, telling the egyptian story of life, death, and rebirth in the afterlife.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='turn first page'>
         As you turn the first page, the translator explains the meanings of the pictures displayed there.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='turn second page'>
         As you turn the next page, the translator explains the meanings of the pictures displayed there.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='turn third page'>
         As you turn the third page, the translator explains the meanings of the pictures displayed there.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='turn fourth page'>
         As you turn the fourth page, the translator explains the meanings of the pictures displayed there.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='not in merchants stall'>
         As you turn the page on the book all you can make out is that the book is written in some ancient language made of pictures.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='drop unlocked book'>
         As the book hits the ground it is scooped up by a young local boy and he dashes off into the crowd. You spend a few moments searching before realizing that it is gone for good.
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='haggle for book'>
         You pretend to browse the selection of books while haggling with the owner of the book seller stall. He finally comes down to a reasonable price of just 42ig for the book. The funds are transfered and you find yourself the proud owner of the mysterious book. Attempts to open it are fruitless and you begin to wonder if the merchant, who is studiously ignoring you now, got the better end of the deal.
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='try to read closed book'>
         The cover of the book reads: Book of the Dead or An Egyptians Guide to Life after Life. If you want to read it, you need to open it first.
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='turn fifth page'>
         As you turn the final page, the translator explains the meanings of the pictures displayed there. As you finish veiwing the images, you close the book.
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='steal book from merchant'>
         As you try to discreetly lift the book from the stall and slip it into your bag, a boy perched atop the wagon starts shrieking at the top of his lungs to the merchant who sees you! He takes your hand and drags you to the magistrate's office (who happens to be his brother in law).
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='steal continued'>
         They gather an impromptu jury with the little boy as a very credible witness. The magistrate listens to your protestations of intent to purchase the book but in the end decides that you aren't very believable. He fines you the cost of the book (which you get to keep) of 100ig plus 200ig in court costs. You are warned not to get caught stealing again or the penalty will be much stiffer.
         </para>

         <para number='14' comment='get book finishing para'>
         You frown in dismay as after leaving the trial you discover that the book you have is locked with no obvious way to open it.  There is however, an indentation in the cover shaped like a beetle of some kind.
         </para>

         <para number='15' comment='have been caught before'>
         The magistrate is not happy to see you before him again as you have obviously not learned your lesson. This time he confiscates the book and charges you a penalty of 500ig for bothering him again.
         </para>

         <para number='16' comment='try to buy book'>
         You pick the book up and try to get his attention. He seems to enjoy the challenge of getting a good price out of the customer more than the sale itself as he is too busy haggling with another customer to notice your attempts to get his attention.
         </para>

         <para number='17' comment='if tries to open, open book'>
         The book is already open!
         </para>

         <para number='18' comment='sell book unlocked'>
         You find the book seller and try to get him to buy the book back from you... After much discussion you are given 15ig for the book and sent on your way.
         </para>

