      <section name='desert'>

         <para number='1' comment='random desert message'>
         The dunes here stretch endlessly in all directions. The path you were following before has vanished leaving you lost in the desert
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='random desert message'>
         You are standing on the edge of a sand storm. The wind is picking up and you see a large cloud of sand headed your way, you must choose which direction before you are trapped in it.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='random desert message'>
         Inside a sand storm. The sand blows so thick around you that all you can do for several hours is hunker down and hope that is passes soon.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='random desert message'>
         Sand dunes are laid out before you as far as the eye can see. You think you can see a shuttle landing off in the distance but aren't sure of the direction due to the blinding sun and the shimmering heat.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='random desert message'>
         He who neglects to drink of the spring of experience is likely to die of thirst in the desert of ignorance. --Ling Po
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='random desert message'>
         Sand everywhere you look, with no discernable way out...
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='random desert message'>
         Old Earth had a saying that: It is better to dwell in the wilderness, than with a contentious and an angry woman.... but looking around this particular desert, you have to wonder.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='random desert message'>
         The wind moves swiftly stirring up the sand and stinging your eyes. You are right on the edge of a massive storm
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='random desert message'>
         The sand billows around you scouring your exposed skin. You hunker down in your robes for a while hoping that the winds will die down eventually. After several hours it is clear that the storm will last much longer than you and your only option is to try and walk out.
         </para>

