      <section name='sapphire'>

         <para number='1' comment='first slow death'>
         As you finally manage to pry the stone free, the ground starts to tremble beneath your feet. A quick glance towards the exit refeals that the door to the tomb has slammed shut trapping you inside!
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='second message'>
         The door seems firmly wedged shut and there is no obvious way for you to open it.  As the oxygen in the room starts to diminish, the torches slowly flicker then go out.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='third message'>
         You click on a flashlight conveniently left behind by another tourist and begin searching in earnest for an exit, but find none.  You wonder if that is voices you hear on the other side of the door. You pound on it furiously but it still doesn't budge.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='forth message'>
         The air begins to feel thicker as you struggle to breathe the oxygen deprived air. Darkness soon closes in around your vision as you black out and pass on to your next life.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='msg in the hosp w unlocked book'>
         You come into awareness and find yourself floating above your body in the embalmer's workshop. The specialists here have made quick work of preparing your body for the afterlife. The organs have been removed and placed in special jars each labeled as to their contents and your body has been carfully wrapped with a mask closely resembling your own face placed over 'your' face.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='message in hosp w/out book'>
         As you wake up, in your own body, you see an angry planetary official cursing the local kids that steal the warning signs. He turns to you as you wake and appologizes profusely stating that due to the fact that your death was a horrible accident, the planet has covered all the cloning costs and has made arrangements with the insurance company to ensure you are not penalized for your adventure.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='Not dead msg when enter tomb'>
         A guard blocks your path. "Only relatives of the dead, or the dead themselves are allowed to enter the tomb. Have some respect!"
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='msg in hosp lockedbook'>
         As your lifeless corpse is moved to the hospital, you are compelled to follow it. You hear the embalmers arguing over whether your remains are to be mummified in accordance with custom as laid out in the book of the dead while the other points out that your copy of the book is locked so you must be a tourist. In the end, they settle on cloning you since you were covered by insurance and they get paid more for cloning.
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='wake up in hospital alive'>
         As you wake up, this time in your own body, you see an angry planetary official berating the embalmers over their delay in cloning you. He turns to you as you wake and appologizes profusely stating that due to the fact that your death was a horrible accident, the planet has covered all the cloning costs and has made arrangements with the insurance company to ensure you are not penalized for your adventure.
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='continuation of 5'>
         As the workers finish their grizzly work, you hear one of them remark "I guess its off to the communal burial chamber for this one." With that, they cart your body off and you are left wondering what you can do next.
         </para>

